<tag>Sigma main event</tag>
<description>{CovLStrv2{The docker service container is configured to permit writing to the root filesystem. This makes some security attack vectors such as privilege escalation, denial-of-service or authorization bypass possible since the container instance's filesystem can be tampered with.}}</description>
<line>5</line>
</event>
<event>
<remediation>true</remediation>
<tag>remediation</tag>
<description>{CovLStrv2{Explicitly set the `read-only` attribute of the service to `true` to create a service container with a read-only filesystem.}}</description>
<line>5</line>
</event>
<extra>container_filesystem_write_docker_compose -- //docker-compose.yml -- ##Σ-markup - ##Σ-markup - services - web</extra>
